50|$|A shy and elusive bird, the <b>mountain</b> <b>peacock-pheasant</b> is {{distributed}} and endemic to montane {{forests of the}} central Malay Peninsula. The diet consists mainly of berries, beetles and ants.|$|E
50|$|Due {{to ongoing}} habitat loss, small {{population}} size and limited range, the <b>mountain</b> <b>peacock-pheasant</b> is evaluated as Vulnerable on the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. It is listed on Appendix III of CITES in Malaysia.|$|E
